Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed-memory supercomputers and their performance in traversing large graphs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses different local data structures and their impact on performance. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the performance and scalability trade-offs of different approaches. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) could be a relevant category as distributed-memory supercomputers rely on network communication. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the application of graph traversal algorithms to real-world problems in science and engineering.
